May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Healing doesn't mean: You have to forgive You won't still have a hard time Things will be easy or pain-free You are giving up or giving in You are showing weakness You are choosing the "right" or "wrong" path @findyourshinetherapy'.

node.text:
Sometimes people worry that when they start to heal from trauma, it will mean that they are handing over their power. "If I acknowledge that it happened and work through my feelings about it, does that mean I'm accepting it?"⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you are on your own path to healing, it is just that: your own. Healing doesn't mean you have to forgive, be happy all of the time, never experience pain anymore, are giving in or showing weakness. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Your healing journey is as personal to you as what you went through. The difference is, you don't have to do healing alone.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jaime Castillo, LCSW in Tempe, Arizona. May be an image of text that says 'As you grow, you might find yourself doing: Less More Reacting Competing People pleasing Defending Sabotaging Running away Chasing Responding Uplifting Communicating Listening Reflecting Facing Trusting @findyourshinetherapy'.

node.text:
Growing might mean:

Less reacting more responding
Less competing more uplifting
Less people pleasing more communicating
Less defending more listening
Less sabotaging more reflecting
Less running away more facing
Less chasing more trusting

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jaime Castillo, LCSW in Tempe, Arizona. May be an image of text that says 'Congratulations to the Person Who: Ended a toxic relationship Fought to keep their relationship alive Left a 9-5 job to pursue a passion Left self-employment for the stability of a 9-5 Sought therapy for a mental health struggle Is on their own elf-healing ourney Left their comfort zone Is returning to what's comfortable Made the more difficult decision Is choosing ease @findyourshinetherapy'.

node.text:
We tend to congratulate one path and one path only: the one that leads us to higher status (financial status, relationship status, life status).

The reality is that many paths deserve to be celebrated. If a decision felt right for you and you made it, that is worth acknowledgement regardless of what others think. Perhaps even moreso if that decision meant trusting yourself rather than following society’s expectations of you.

Sending you love today💛

Criticism "You always rely on me! Can you do anything yourself?" "I'm not willing to have this conversation right now." "Why do you always have to bring this up?" "I won't allow you to criticize me." "You're such an asshole!" "I can't respond to your texts while am working." "Why are you so needy all the time?" "I need to take some time to collect my thoughts." "You are so impossible to deal with!" @findyourshinetherapy'.

node.text:
I mentioned in yesterday's post that boundaries are not an excuse to demean someone else.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Boundaries help preserve the health of a relationship, while criticism does the opposite. Notice the themes in the two columns: all of the boundary statements start with "I", while all of the criticisms include "you." That's because boundaries truly are about you and your limits, while criticisms are attacks that center the other person.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
As always, love to hear your thoughts!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
